1. DESCRIPTION OF SOFTWARE

Template Builder is a Command-Line Interface (CLI) tool that allows users to create custom project templates from YAML configuration files. The tool generates ready-made project structures by creating folders, generating files, and collecting user input through interactive CLI prompts defined in YAML files.

The Software enables users to:
- Define project templates using YAML configuration files
- Generate project structures automatically
- Create files and folders based on template definitions
- Collect user input through interactive prompts
- Use template variables and functions for dynamic content generation

